class Solution {
    public int distanceBetweenBusStops(int[] distance, int start, int destination) {
        int clockwiseDistance = 0;
        int totalDistance = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < distance.length; i++) {
            if ((start < destination && i >= start && i < destination) || 
                (start > destination && (i >= start || i < destination))) {
                clockwiseDistance += distance[i];
            }
            totalDistance += distance[i];
        }

        return Math.min(clockwiseDistance, totalDistance - clockwiseDistance);
    }
}
```

This code defines a method `distanceBetweenBusStops` which takes an array `distance`, and two integers `start` and `destination`. It calculates the minimum distance between two bus stops on a circular route.
